data.chText: 认为我们能在两个月之内完成这项工作，这完全是不切实际的。
data.enText: It was totally impractical to think that we could finish the job in two months.

data.chText: 手不灵巧的；不善于规划（或组织）的
data.enText: not good at doing things that involve using the hands; not good at planning or organizing things

tr: not workable or not given to practical matters
example: refloating the ship proved impractical because of the expense
he is intelligent but too impractical for commercial work

value.def: If you describe an object, idea, or course of action as impractical, you mean that it is not sensible or realistic, and does not work well in practice.

example.ex: When stalking subjects, a tripod is impractical...
example.tran: 潜步跟踪目标时,用三脚架是不切实际的。

example.ex: It became impractical to make a business trip by ocean liner.
example.tran: 乘坐远洋班轮进行商务旅行变得不合时宜了。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf

value.tran: 不切实际的;不现实的;不可行的

value.def: If you describe someone as impractical, you mean that they do not have the abilities or skills to do practical work such as making, repairing, or organizing things.

example.ex: Geniuses are supposed to be eccentric and hopelessly impractical.
example.tran: 天才通常都被认为行为古怪而且毫无实践能力。

value.tran: 无动手能力的;无实践能力的
